<br>
See Every Zone in the game (bah - didn't bother with PoM)<br>
Get a good haste item (man I lost a lot of rolls early on)<br>
Get 3k unbuffed HP<br>
<br>
By the time I retired, I pretty much acheived my goals - and did so with a great group of people (Lotus Cult on Quellious).<br>
<br>
I don't remember my exact unbuffed stats in the end. But I remember they were well over 1250 AC and 3400 HP.<br>
<br>
It's just my opinion but it's about percentages too. 300 HP gain at level 50+ isn't that much really, and unless you're getting CH'd, it doesn't really matter in a group. Solo, you can last longer with more HP.<br>
<br>
But AC between 1000 to about 1300 makes a big difference I've found.<br>
<br>
I haven't played a character that was as good as my monk was in a long time. Maybe things have changed where AC doesn't matter as much.<br>
<br>
I used to preach HP above all else (mainly because I always had a raid mentallity and I had great gear regardless for the last year or so that I played).<br>
<br>
I looked at things from my own perspective too much. I'm just looking at those two profiles now and between the two, I'd choose the AC profile is all *grin* <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#778899><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ufondiler.showPublicProfile?language=EN>fondiler</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ewtoo.org/~matt/monkey/02thumb.jpg" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Young Grasshoppah</span><br>  Posts: 47<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(9/26/02 7:41:14 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=11595.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: HP vs AC?</span><hr size=1> I used to be   AC..STR nut but ive heard so much about hp that now thats all i can think about...is brain washing legal on EQ? can i petition hehe <p>THE FOND
